        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare T-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma characterized by monomorphic cytomorphology and epitheliotropism. It is mostly detected in the small intestine but can also be present in the colon duodenum orand stomach. It is an aggressive tumor that can disseminate to mesenteric lymph nodes lung liver brain and skin. Major clinical features include abdominal pain gastrointestinal bleeding obstruction or perforation diarrhoea and weight loss. It is not associated to coeliac disease."
        },
